The distinctive red color often influences the naming of hot springs as "Akayu." However, not all Akayu are red; for instance, the {{ill|Akayu Onsen (Yamagata)|ja|赤湯温泉 (山形県)}} in {{ill|Yamagata Prefecture|ja|山形県}} features clear, colorless water. This name was derived from local {{ill|Open Spring Legends|ja|開湯伝説}} rather than the water's appearance.
